Couldn’t bring my daughter with me to Bonnaroo so I did the next best thing 😂 to be completely honest, waking up at 4:45 AM to fly across the country today was a little tough. But part of being a good dad is getting shit done and setting a good example. I feel really fortunate my daughter gets to grow up watching her dad truly live his dream to make a living - she’ll always know that no dream or goal out of reach. So thank you guys for being here with me on the journey. Hopefully next year she’ll be up on my shoulders on stage 😂 everyone wish your dads a very very happy Father’s Day! Much love
1 Dad. 1 Farm. A whole shitload of ravers and an abundance of energy and good times. Fathers Day @bonnaroo Edition was a great success 😎 one of the sickest crowds I’ve seen in a while!!

Normally when I write a new song I play it in my sets for 6 months to a year before I put it out… this song was different. I kept it close, under wraps, and played it for the first time ever last weekend. The goosebumps I felt watching everyone hear the chorus for the first time was something I’ve never really experienced before. This song is so special to me and I hope you guys love it like I do. Lights Go Out is out everywhere now, go stream that shit ❤️ (link in bio)

My beautiful baby girl turns one year old today. To say it’s my proudest achievement so far in life would be an understatement - nothing I’ve done in life compares to watching this little thing grow so much, so fast every single day. From her first smile to her first words, to watching her amazing personality blossom is really beyond words. This is just the start of such an incredible adventure together and I can’t wait to see where life takes us. I love you more than I could ever explain Callie, and I’m so proud to be your dad ❤️
Thanks for getting Wicked with me Los Angeles 😈 now off to enjoy time with the fam till NYE… and then, much more of this to come 🤫 Stay tuned

Thought my days of throwing myself into the ground at high speeds were far behind me, but destiny decided to give me one final giant reality check. Took a 4x4 (swipe left) for a pretty sweet barrel roll going 50 MPH, and shattered my wrist, forearm and elbow all in one go. Beyond grateful it was just an arm and not my neck, head, back etc. Grateful I made it out alive and in one piece. Grateful I get to be back home w my family to have surgery and recover. And incredibly grateful to my brothers who were there to pick me up when I was down. Not sure how long I’ll be out of it until I have surgery Tuesday, but cross your fingers for me, tell your friends and family u love them, and wear your seatbelts!!!
